# 🩺 GlucoseGuard PK

AI-Assisted Diabetes Triage and Referral Support System for Pakistan

---

## 🌍 The Problem

Pakistan has 33 million diabetics — the 3rd highest in the world.
Over 50% remain undiagnosed.

Community health workers running rural screening camps have no fast
intelligent triage tool. They screen hundreds of patients manually
with no way to prioritize who needs urgent referral.

GlucoseGuard PK changes that.

---

## 🩺 What It Does

- 🎯 Predicts diabetes risk instantly from basic health indicators
- 🟢🟡🔴 Returns Low, Medium, or High risk classification
- 🔍 Explains top 5 risk drivers using SHAP explainability
- 📋 Recommends next action — lifestyle advice, retest, or refer for HbA1c
- 👥 Generates population-level summaries for NGO screening camps

---

## 📊 Machine Learning Pipeline

- Dataset — CDC BRFSS 2015 with 80,000+ health records
- Models Evaluated — Logistic Regression, Random Forest, XGBoost
- Selected Model — Logistic Regression
- Diabetic Recall — 76%
- ROC-AUC Score — 0.81
- Class Imbalance — Handled with SMOTE
- Explainability — SHAP LinearExplainer
- Deployment — Streamlit Cloud

### Why Logistic Regression?

For a health screening tool, missing a diabetic patient is dangerous.
Logistic Regression achieved 76% recall on diabetic cases compared
to XGBoost's 18% — making it the clinically safer choice for triage.

